{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/sarif-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "PMD",
          "version": "7.22.0",
          "informationUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/latest/",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "ExcessiveImports",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A high number of imports (66) can indicate a high degree of coupling within an object; current threshold is 30."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nA high number of imports can indicate a high degree of coupling within an object. This rule\ncounts the number of unique imports and reports a violation if the count is above the\nuser-specified threshold.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_design.html#excessiveimports",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nA high number of imports can indicate a high degree of coupling within an object. This rule\ncounts the number of unique imports and reports a violation if the count is above the\nuser-specified threshold.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Design",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Design"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CouplingBetweenObjects",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A value of 52 may denote a high amount of coupling within the class (threshold: 20)"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nThis rule counts the number of unique attributes, local variables, and return types within an object.\nA number higher than the specified threshold can indicate a high degree of coupling.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_design.html#couplingbetweenobjects",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nThis rule counts the number of unique attributes, local variables, and return types within an object.\nA number higher than the specified threshold can indicate a high degree of coupling.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Design",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Design"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "TooManyMethods",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "This class has too many methods, consider refactoring it."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nA class with too many methods is probably a good suspect for refactoring, in order to reduce its\ncomplexity and find a way to have more fine grained objects.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_design.html#toomanymethods",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nA class with too many methods is probably a good suspect for refactoring, in order to reduce its\ncomplexity and find a way to have more fine grained objects.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Design",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Design"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CommentRequired",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Field comments are required"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nDenotes whether javadoc (formal) comments are required (or unwanted) for specific language elements.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_documentation.html#commentrequired",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nDenotes whether javadoc (formal) comments are required (or unwanted) for specific language elements.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Documentation",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Documentation"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AvoidFieldNameMatchingMethodName",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Field connect has the same name as a method"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nIt can be confusing to have a field name with the same name as a method. While this is permitted,\nhaving information (field) and actions (method) is not clear naming. Developers versed in\nSmalltalk often prefer this approach as the methods denote accessor methods.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_errorprone.html#avoidfieldnamematchingmethodname",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nIt can be confusing to have a field name with the same name as a method. While this is permitted,\nhaving information (field) and actions (method) is not clear naming. Developers versed in\nSmalltalk often prefer this approach as the methods denote accessor methods.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Error Prone",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Error Prone"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AvoidFieldNameMatchingMethodName",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Field pushEntries has the same name as a method"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nIt can be confusing to have a field name with the same name as a method. While this is permitted,\nhaving information (field) and actions (method) is not clear naming. Developers versed in\nSmalltalk often prefer this approach as the methods denote accessor methods.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_errorprone.html#avoidfieldnamematchingmethodname",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nIt can be confusing to have a field name with the same name as a method. While this is permitted,\nhaving information (field) and actions (method) is not clear naming. Developers versed in\nSmalltalk often prefer this approach as the methods denote accessor methods.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Error Prone",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Error Prone"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "LongVariable",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Avoid excessively long variable names like pushEntriesAdvanced"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nFields, formal arguments, or local variable names that are too long can make the code difficult to follow.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_codestyle.html#longvariable",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nFields, formal arguments, or local variable names that are too long can make the code difficult to follow.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Code Style",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Code Style"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
